Require the Local Chief Executive as the responsible of the Agri-Pinoy Rice Processing Center II pending to the turn-over to San Isidro Lower Women’s Multi-purpose Cooperative (SILWMPC) as the beneficiary to issue and file the same to the Commission Proper through the Audit Team and Regional Director of Commission on Audit Region 10:

i. Notice of Loss of Government Property

ii. Request for Relief of Accountability accompanied by the following documents:
The basic notice of loss showing the exact date of filing and receipt in the Office of the Auditor concerned or the COA;
Affidavit of the accountable officer containing a statement of facts and circumstances of the loss, i.e. property lost and its valuation, actual date in which the absence was first noted, manner of disappearance, efforts exerted to recover the same, provisions made to safeguard the property, date when the loss was reported to the auditor and police authorities, etc., 
Affidavits of two (2) disinterested persons cognizant of the facts and circumstances of the loss;
Final investigation report of the office or department head, proper government investigating agency (PNP, BFP, NBI, etc.); 
Comment/s and/or recommendation of the agency head;
List and description including book value, date of acquisition, property number, account classification, condition of the property, and other additional relevant information of the properties lost as attested by the concerned officials, as the case may be; 
Authenticated pictures of the site (loss through fire and theft or robbery/holdup; and
Comments and/or recommendation of the auditor. 

 Require the Municipal Engineer (noted by the Local Chief Executive) to justify in written form the delay in the filing of the aforesaid notice and request with satisfactory explanation or the reason(s) for such delay which should be verified or confirmed by the Audit Team.

Require the concerned Barangays, NGAs and NGOs/POs to submit the following documentary requirements, where applicable, as prescribed under Section 3.0 of COA Circular No. 2012-001 dated June 14, 2012:

Fund utilization reports, indicating the summary of expense and the status report of accomplishments, certified by the accountant, approved by the Local Chief Executive/Head of the receiving parties and verified by the internal auditor or equivalent official of the Municipality;
Pictures of implemented projects/programs/activities, if any;
Inspection reports and certificates of project completion issued by the Municipal Engineer Officer’s authorized representative, if any;
Lists of beneficiaries with their signatures signifying their acceptance/acknowledgment of the projects/funds/goods/services received;
Proof of verification by the city official of the validity of the documents submitted by the receiving parties;
Copies of the Official Receipts issued by the receiving parties  acknowledging receipt of funds transferred;
ORs issued by the Municipal Treasurer acknowledging return by the receiving parties of any unutilized/excess amount of the funds released; and
Liquidation Reports.

Subsequently, correcting entries should be effected on the recording of funds released to the various Barangays, NGAs and NGOs/POs. Hence, the accounts Due from LGUs, Due from NGAs and Due from NGOs/POs should be debited to record the release of funds to the said Barangays, NGAs and NGOs/POs for the implementation of projects/programs/activities, and credit these accounts for the liquidation of the subject funds. 

Review all liquidation reports to ensure that funds are spent for its intended public purpose only. The rationale of the provision is to ensure that public funds will not be used as payment for private purposes or for purposes not within the intention of the source agency. 

Refrain from incurring unnecessary expenditure of government funds to preclude loss of wastage thereof and limit expenses to those which are essential and supportive of the implementation of the objectives and mission of the LGU.

